Date: 21/5/1875
Source: Otago Daily Times
Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: As one of the first tenants on the Maori Reserve, Princes street, when squatting licenses for 12 months were granted by the provincial Government, and afterwards a tenant on the Manse Reserve since 1865, and when erecting a stone building on that reserve I was asked by John Millar, Esq., F.S.A., City Engineer, if I would consent to erect iron instead of stone, 33ft from the building line of Princes street, as a few gentlemen had in contemplation the widening of Princes street on the east side.
